HEADWORD: Phosphoroscope
<hw>Phos*phor"o*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Phosphorus</ets> + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An apparatus for observing the phosphorescence
produced in different bodies by the action of light, and for measuring
its duration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Phosphorous</ent>⟦br⟧
